IV. Special Abilities
Standing Stone Ability: Atronach's Gift & The Souls' Ward
Spell Absorption: Nora's connection to the Atronach stone, amplified by the protective spirits of her parents, allows her to absorb the energy of hostile spells. She can use this ability three times per combat. Each time she is the target of a hostile spell, she can choose to negate its effect and regain FP equal to its cost.
Drawback: Her natural FP recovery is poor; she does not regain FP during a Short Rest.
The Parent's Souls (The Burden)
The two black soul gems she carries are a source of constant, low-level psychic distress. In any situation involving Daedra, the undead, or soul trapping, the gems will begin to pulse with a faint, cold light, and she must make a Guile roll to maintain her concentration on complex tasks.
This is not just an item; it is the core of her personal quest: to find a way to free her parents from the Soul Cairn.
The Uncontrolled Power (Trauma Response)
In moments of extreme stress or when a Daedra is present, the GM may call for a Guile check. On a failure, Nora's innate Conjuration mastery lashes out instinctively. This is not under her control. It might manifest as:
A powerful, un-aimed Banish Daedra effect
The instant dissolution of a summoned creature
The silencing of all magic in a small area
The shattering of an enchanted weapon
The redirecting or stealing of control over a summoned entity
She will immediately be horrified by what she has done, viewing it as a catastrophic loss of control rather than a display of power.

